Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). In a medium saucepan over medium heat, saute onion until translucent. Stir in flour, milk, mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, sugar and salt; cook, stirring, until thickened. Place green beans in a 9x13 inch baking dish; pour cheese sauce over green beans. In a small bowl combine bread crumbs and egg. Spread over green beans. Bake in preheated oven for 40 minutes.